Package hydra.ext.org.iana.linkrelations

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LinkRelationType.PartialVisitor<R>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    LinkRelationType
    An IANA link relation type
    LinkRelationType.About
    Refers to a resource that is the subject of the link's context.
    LinkRelationType.Acl
    Asserts that the link target provides an access control resource for the link context.
    LinkRelationType.Alternate
    Refers to a substitute for this context [HTML]
    LinkRelationType.Amphtml
    Used to reference alternative content that uses the AMP profile of the HTML format.
    LinkRelationType.Appendix
    Refers to an appendix.
    LinkRelationType.Apple_touch_icon
    Refers to an icon for the context.
    LinkRelationType.Apple_touch_startup_image
    Refers to a launch screen for the context.
    LinkRelationType.Archives
    Refers to a collection of records, documents, or other materials of historical interest.
    LinkRelationType.Author
    Refers to the context's author.
    LinkRelationType.Blocked_by
    Identifies the entity that blocks access to a resource following receipt of a legal demand.
    LinkRelationType.Bookmark
    Gives a permanent link to use for bookmarking purposes.
    LinkRelationType.Canonical
    Designates the preferred version of a resource (the IRI and its contents).
    LinkRelationType.Chapter
    Refers to a chapter in a collection of resources.
    LinkRelationType.Cite_as
    Indicates that the link target is preferred over the link context for the purpose of permanent citation.
    LinkRelationType.Collection
    The target IRI points to a resource which represents the collection resource for the context IRI.
    LinkRelationType.Contents
    Refers to a table of contents.
    LinkRelationType.Convertedfrom
    The document linked to was later converted to the document that contains this link relation.
    LinkRelationType.Copyright
    Refers to a copyright statement that applies to the link's context.
    LinkRelationType.Create_form
    The target IRI points to a resource where a submission form can be obtained.
    LinkRelationType.Current
    Refers to a resource containing the most recent item(s) in a collection of resources.
    LinkRelationType.Describedby
    Refers to a resource providing information about the link's context.
    LinkRelationType.Describes
    The relationship A 'describes' B asserts that resource A provides a description of resource B.
    LinkRelationType.Disclosure
    Refers to a list of patent disclosures made with respect to material for which 'disclosure' relation is specified.
    LinkRelationType.Dns_prefetch
    Used to indicate an origin that will be used to fetch required resources for the link context, and that the user agent ought to resolve as early as possible.
    LinkRelationType.Duplicate
    Refers to a resource whose available representations are byte-for-byte identical with the corresponding representations of the context IRI.
    LinkRelationType.Edit
    Refers to a resource that can be used to edit the link's context.
    LinkRelationType.Edit_form
    The target IRI points to a resource where a submission form for editing associated resource can be obtained.
    LinkRelationType.Edit_media
    Refers to a resource that can be used to edit media associated with the link's context.
    LinkRelationType.Enclosure
    Identifies a related resource that is potentially large and might require special handling.
    LinkRelationType.External
    Refers to a resource that is not part of the same site as the current context.
    LinkRelationType.First
    An IRI that refers to the furthest preceding resource in a series of resources.
    LinkRelationType.Glossary
    Refers to a glossary of terms.
    LinkRelationType.Help
    Refers to context-sensitive help.
    LinkRelationType.Hosts
    Refers to a resource hosted by the server indicated by the link context.
    LinkRelationType.Hub
    Refers to a hub that enables registration for notification of updates to the context.
    LinkRelationType.Icon
    Refers to an icon representing the link's context.
    LinkRelationType.Index
    Refers to an index.
    LinkRelationType.Intervalafter
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval that ends before the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.21
    LinkRelationType.Intervalbefore
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval that begins after the end of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.22
    LinkRelationType.Intervalcontains
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval that begins after the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource, and ends before the end of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.23
    LinkRelationType.Intervaldisjoint
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval that begins after the end of the time interval associated with the context resource, or ends before the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.24
    LinkRelationType.Intervalduring
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval that begins before the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource, and ends after the end of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.25
    LinkRelationType.Intervalequals
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval whose beginning coincides with the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource, and whose end coincides with the end of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.26
    LinkRelationType.Intervalfinishedby
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval that begins after the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource, and whose end coincides with the end of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.27
    LinkRelationType.Intervalfinishes
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval that begins before the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource, and whose end coincides with the end of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.28
    LinkRelationType.Intervalin
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval that begins before or is coincident with the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource, and ends after or is coincident with the end of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.29
    LinkRelationType.Intervalmeets
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval whose beginning coincides with the end of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.30
    LinkRelationType.Intervalmetby
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval whose end coincides with the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.31
    LinkRelationType.Intervaloverlappedby
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval that begins before the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource, and ends after the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.32
    LinkRelationType.Intervaloverlaps
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval that begins before the end of the time interval associated with the context resource, and ends after the end of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.33
    LinkRelationType.Intervalstartedby
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval whose beginning coincides with the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource, and ends before the end of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.34
    LinkRelationType.Intervalstarts
    refers to a resource associated with a time interval whose beginning coincides with the beginning of the time interval associated with the context resource, and ends after the end of the time interval associated with the context resource [Time Ontology in OWL] section 4.2.35
    LinkRelationType.Item
    The target IRI points to a resource that is a member of the collection represented by the context IRI.
    LinkRelationType.Last
    An IRI that refers to the furthest following resource in a series of resources.
    LinkRelationType.Latest_version
    Points to a resource containing the latest (e.g., current) version of the context.
    LinkRelationType.License
    Refers to a license associated with this context.
    LinkRelationType.Linkset
    The link target of a link with the "linkset" relation type provides a set of links, including links in which the link context of the link participates.
    LinkRelationType.Lrdd
    Refers to further information about the link's context, expressed as a LRDD ("Link-based Resource Descriptor Document") resource.
    LinkRelationType.Manifest
    Links to a manifest file for the context.
    LinkRelationType.Mask_icon
    Refers to a mask that can be applied to the icon for the context.
    LinkRelationType.Media_feed
    Refers to a feed of personalised media recommendations relevant to the link context.
    LinkRelationType.Memento
    The Target IRI points to a Memento, a fixed resource that will not change state anymore.
    LinkRelationType.Micropub
    Links to the context's Micropub endpoint.
    LinkRelationType.Modulepreload
    Refers to a module that the user agent is to preemptively fetch and store for use in the current context.
    LinkRelationType.Monitor
    Refers to a resource that can be used to monitor changes in an HTTP resource.
    LinkRelationType.Monitor_group
    Refers to a resource that can be used to monitor changes in a specified group of HTTP resources.
    LinkRelationType.Next
    Indicates that the link's context is a part of a series, and that the next in the series is the link target.
    LinkRelationType.Next_archive
    Refers to the immediately following archive resource.
    LinkRelationType.Nofollow
    Indicates that the context’s original author or publisher does not endorse the link target.
    LinkRelationType.Noopener
    Indicates that any newly created top-level browsing context which results from following the link will not be an auxiliary browsing context.
    LinkRelationType.Noreferrer
    Indicates that no referrer information is to be leaked when following the link.
    LinkRelationType.Opener
    Indicates that any newly created top-level browsing context which results from following the link will be an auxiliary browsing context.
    LinkRelationType.Openid2_local_id
    Refers to an OpenID Authentication server on which the context relies for an assertion that the end user controls an Identifier.
    LinkRelationType.Openid2_provider
    Refers to a resource which accepts OpenID Authentication protocol messages for the context.
    LinkRelationType.Original
    The Target IRI points to an Original Resource.
    LinkRelationType.P3pv1
    Refers to a P3P privacy policy for the context.
    LinkRelationType.Payment
    Indicates a resource where payment is accepted.
    LinkRelationType.Pingback
    Gives the address of the pingback resource for the link context.
    LinkRelationType.Preconnect
    Used to indicate an origin that will be used to fetch required resources for the link context.
    LinkRelationType.Predecessor_version
    Points to a resource containing the predecessor version in the version history.
    LinkRelationType.Prefetch
    The prefetch link relation type is used to identify a resource that might be required by the next navigation from the link context, and that the user agent ought to fetch, such that the user agent can deliver a faster response once the resource is requested in the future.
    LinkRelationType.Preload
    Refers to a resource that should be loaded early in the processing of the link's context, without blocking rendering.
    LinkRelationType.Prerender
    Used to identify a resource that might be required by the next navigation from the link context, and that the user agent ought to fetch and execute, such that the user agent can deliver a faster response once the resource is requested in the future.
    LinkRelationType.Prev
    Indicates that the link's context is a part of a series, and that the previous in the series is the link target.
    LinkRelationType.Prev_archive
    Refers to the immediately preceding archive resource.
    LinkRelationType.Preview
    Refers to a resource that provides a preview of the link's context.
    LinkRelationType.Previous
    Refers to the previous resource in an ordered series of resources.
    LinkRelationType.Privacy_policy
    Refers to a privacy policy associated with the link's context.
    LinkRelationType.Profile
    Identifying that a resource representation conforms to a certain profile, without affecting the non-profile semantics of the resource representation.
    LinkRelationType.Publication
    Links to a publication manifest.
    LinkRelationType.Related
    Identifies a related resource.
    LinkRelationType.Replies
    Identifies a resource that is a reply to the context of the link.
    LinkRelationType.Restconf
    Identifies the root of RESTCONF API as configured on this HTTP server.
    LinkRelationType.Ruleinput
    The resource identified by the link target provides an input value to an instance of a rule, where the resource which represents the rule instance is identified by the link context.
    LinkRelationType.Search
    Refers to a resource that can be used to search through the link's context and related resources.
    LinkRelationType.Section
    Refers to a section in a collection of resources.
    LinkRelationType.Self
    Conveys an identifier for the link's context.
    LinkRelationType.Service
    Indicates a URI that can be used to retrieve a service document.
    LinkRelationType.Service_desc
    Identifies service description for the context that is primarily intended for consumption by machines.
    LinkRelationType.Service_doc
    Identifies service documentation for the context that is primarily intended for human consumption.
    LinkRelationType.Service_meta
    Identifies general metadata for the context that is primarily intended for consumption by machines.
    LinkRelationType.Siptrunkingcapability
    refers to a capability document that defines parameters or configuration requirements for automated peering and communication channel negotiation of the Session Initiation Protocol (SIP).
    LinkRelationType.Sponsored
    Refers to a resource that is within a context that is sponsored (such as advertising or another compensation agreement).
    LinkRelationType.Start
    Refers to the first resource in a collection of resources.
    LinkRelationType.Status
    Identifies a resource that represents the context's status.
    LinkRelationType.Stylesheet
    Refers to a stylesheet.
    LinkRelationType.Subsection
    Refers to a resource serving as a subsection in a collection of resources.
    LinkRelationType.Successor_version
    Points to a resource containing the successor version in the version history.
    LinkRelationType.Sunset
    Identifies a resource that provides information about the context's retirement policy.
    LinkRelationType.Tag
    Gives a tag (identified by the given address) that applies to the current document.
    LinkRelationType.Terms_of_service
    Refers to the terms of service associated with the link's context.
    LinkRelationType.Timegate
    The Target IRI points to a TimeGate for an Original Resource.
    LinkRelationType.Timemap
    The Target IRI points to a TimeMap for an Original Resource.
    LinkRelationType.Type
    Refers to a resource identifying the abstract semantic type of which the link's context is considered to be an instance.
    LinkRelationType.Ugc
    Refers to a resource that is within a context that is User Generated Content.
    LinkRelationType.Up
    Refers to a parent document in a hierarchy of documents.
    LinkRelationType.Version_history
    Points to a resource containing the version history for the context.
    LinkRelationType.Via
    Identifies a resource that is the source of the information in the link's context.
    LinkRelationType.Webmention
    Identifies a target URI that supports the Webmention protocol.
    LinkRelationType.Working_copy
    Points to a working copy for this resource.
    LinkRelationType.Working_copy_of
    Points to the versioned resource from which this working copy was obtained.
